## Laptop strain: same desktop bundle as workstation, plus laptop firmware bits.
## NOTE: no tlp. On 24.04 tlp CONFLICTS with power-profiles-daemon (pulled in by
## ubuntu-desktop-minimal) -> "held broken packages", and it would fight the
## mode-switcher, which drives power via powerprofilesctl (power-profiles-daemon).
## So laptop power management = power-profiles-daemon + distro-modectl's governor
## control: the GNOME-integrated, conflict-free path.
ubuntu-desktop-minimal
flatpak
gnome-shell-extensions
gnome-tweaks
## gamemode/mangohud/winetricks are Gaming-mode-exclusive light packages; the
## trailing omit-sentinel lets a REFRACT_OMIT_MODES=gaming build strip them
## (build.sh drops the sentinel on kept builds). See iso/build.sh.
gamemode  #@omit-if-no:gaming
mangohud  #@omit-if-no:gaming
winetricks  #@omit-if-no:gaming
fwupd
laptop-detect
## Intel-laptop essentials (first real flash target is an Intel ThinkPad X1
## Carbon). intel-media-va-driver-non-free = VAAPI HW video decode on Iris Xe/UHD
## (without it, 4K/H.265 playback falls back to CPU -> hot, loud, battery drain).
## thermald = Intel thermal daemon (prevents aggressive throttling on thin
## chassis; self-disables on non-Intel/AMD). fprintd + libpam-fprintd = the
## fingerprint-reader stack so GNOME Settings can actually enroll the X1's sensor.
intel-media-va-driver-non-free
thermald
fprintd
libpam-fprintd
## Vulkan userspace — REQUIRED for AI mode to use the Arc iGPU. The HWE kernel
## (6.17, installed by build.sh --linux-flavours generic-hwe-24.04) enumerates
## Lunar Lake's Xe2 in-kernel, but without a Vulkan ICD + loader NOTHING in
## userspace can touch the GPU for compute -- Ollama's Vulkan backend (the only
## in-tree path to the Arc 140V; Ollama has no Intel/SYCL/NPU support) would
## find no device and fall to CPU. mesa-vulkan-drivers ships the ANV Intel
## Vulkan driver; without it a Vulkan query returns only llvmpipe (software).
## vulkan-tools provides vulkaninfo, which distro-ai-detect-tier uses to tell a
## real Arc apart from an llvmpipe (kernel/Mesa too old) fallback.
mesa-vulkan-drivers
libvulkan1
vulkan-tools
